4. That Baptiſm is Dipping, appears from Scripture-Metaphors explaining it:Luke 15.50. 
                  Our Lord's Sufferings are called a Baptiſm, becauſe his Pains were not only upon one part of his Body,No ſuch thing as Sprinkling or Rantizing uſed in the Apoſtles Days, nor many Ages after. Mede's Diatribe. but his whole Soul and Body was baptized and plunged into Sorrows. Thus one that is Baptized, is plunged under Water, to ſhew how Chriſt was Baptized and plunged into Sorrows for Man's ſake. Great Meaſures of the Spirit are alſo diſcovered, by Perſons being ſaid to be Baptized with the Spirit;
                  Acts 1.5. for where the word Baptiſm is uſed, whether it be joined with Suffering, with the Spirit, or with Water, it always holds forth a great quantity, either of Sufferings, of the Spirit, or Water.
